{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884559618,"sessionID":"ses_2850888eeffe6nUnso1RhMHTNb","part":{"id":"prt_d7af7a022001EnhMqdmzzVCNjk","messageID":"msg_d7af78bca001ICMmzj1WlWakVK","sessionID":"ses_2850888eeffe6nUnso1RhMHTNb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_a937a06b724c469694fdb226","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Proposal: E2E Integration Testing Framework\n\n## AR Information\n- **AR ID**: AR-041\n- **Module**: test/e2e\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n\n## 1. Purpose\n\nThis proposal outlines the development of an End-to-End (E2E) integration testing framework for the agentcube project. The E2E tests will validate the complete workflow of the Kubernetes custom resources `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` from the perspective of a real user or external system interacting with the cluster.\n\n### Goals\n- Verify the complete lifecycle of `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources\n- Ensure the client-go generated code works correctly in real cluster scenarios\n- Validate controller behavior through API interactions\n- Provide regression testing for system integrations\n\n## 2. Scope\n\n### In Scope\n1. **Test Resources**\n   - `AgentRuntime` CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)\n   - `CodeInterpreter` CRUD operations\n   - Status updates and condition propagation\n   - Resource watching and event handling\n\n2. **Test Infrastructure**\n   - Test framework setup using Go's testing package\n   - Kubernetes test environment (kind cluster or similar)\n   - Test fixtures and helpers for resource creation\n   - Cleanup and teardown utilities\n\n3. **Test Scenarios**\n   - Basic CRUD operations via client-go\n   - Informer-based resource synchronization\n   - Cross-resource dependencies (if applicable)\n   - Error handling and validation\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Performance benchmarking\n- Chaos testing\n- Multi-cluster scenarios\n- Upgrade/migration testing\n- Unit tests for individual components\n\n### Dependencies\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` (provided by deployment/client-go.md)\n- Kubernetes test infrastructure (kubetest, kind, etc.)\n- Go 1.21+\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis\n\n### Positive Impacts\n- **Reliability**: Catch regressions before deployment to production\n- **Developer Experience**: Enable TDD workflow for feature development\n- **Documentation**: Tests serve as executable documentation of expected behavior\n- **Confidence**: Validate client-go generation correctness\n\n### Risks and Mitigations\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| Flaky tests due to timing | Medium | Use retry mechanisms, proper wait utilities |\n| Test environment setup complexity | High | Provide detailed setup scripts, use lightweight clusters |\n| Maintenance burden | Medium | Keep tests focused, regular cleanup of dead code |\n| Long test execution time | Medium | Parallelize tests where possible, use test suites |\n\n### Estimated Effort\n- Framework setup: 2 days\n- Basic CRUD tests: 3 days\n- Informer/watch tests: 2 days\n- Integration with CI: 1 day\n- Documentation and cleanup: 1 day\n- **Total**: ~9 person-days\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option A: Ginkgo/Gomega Framework\n- **Pros**: BDD syntax, rich matchers, good reporting\n- **Cons**: Additional dependency, learning curve for team\n- **Decision**: Use standard Go testing package for simplicity\n\n### Option B: k8s e2e Framework\n- **Pros**: Industry standard, rich utilities\n- **Cons**: Heavyweight, steep learning curve\n- **Decision**: Reject - too complex for this module\n\n### Option C: Operator SDK Tests\n- **Pros**: Built for operators, envtest support\n- **Cons**: May not fit exact needs, additional abstraction\n- **Decision**: Consider for future if controller testing needed\n\n### Selected Approach\nUse standard Go `testing` package with:\n- `client-go` for API interactions\n- `envtest` for controller testing (optional)\n- Custom test helpers for resource management\n\n## 5. Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Setup (Week 1)\n- Create test/e2e directory structure\n- Implement test environment setup\n- Add Makefile targets for test execution\n\n### Phase 2: Core Tests (Week 2)\n- AgentRuntime CRUD tests\n- CodeInterpreter CRUD tests\n- Basic status validation\n\n### Phase 3: Advanced Tests (Week 3)\n- Informer-based tests\n- Watch event validation\n- Cross-resource scenarios\n\n### Phase 4: CI Integration (Week 4)\n- Add to existing CI pipeline\n- Configure test reporting\n- Document execution instructions\n\n## 6. File Structure\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ README.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Makefile\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ go.mod\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ go.sum\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ main_test.go        # Test suite setup\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ setup_test.go       # Environment setup\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentruntime_test.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ codeinterpreter_test.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ helpers/\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ client.go       # Client initialization\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ fixtures.go     # Test data\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ cleanup.go      # Resource cleanup\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ scripts/\n    Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ setup-kind.sh   # Kind cluster setup\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ run-tests.sh    # Test execution\n```\n\n## 7. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All CRUD operations tested for AgentRuntime\n- [ ] All CRUD operations tested for CodeInterpreter\n- [ ] Tests can run against local kind cluster\n- [ ] Tests integrate with existing CI pipeline\n- [ ] Documentation covers test execution and development\n- [ ] Test execution time < 10 minutes","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775884559610,"end":1775884559615}}}}
