{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884565270,"sessionID":"ses_2850888eeffe6nUnso1RhMHTNb","part":{"id":"prt_d7af7f925001YTMabXGP79q6z1","messageID":"msg_d7af7e538001WSQX5zXGh3JzAm","sessionID":"ses_2850888eeffe6nUnso1RhMHTNb","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_fb1ee5df1f1f4fdb857eed96","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-035 ŌĆö client-go ń▒╗Õ×ŗÕ«óµłĘń½»ńö¤µłÉ\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Generate Kubernetes client code (client-go) for AgentCube's API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, enabling in-cluster clients to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. This generated client follows the standard Kubernetes client-go patterns, providing typed clients, listers, informers, and fake clients for testing. The client library will be consumed by the Router component to manage agent runtimes and code interpreters programmatically.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### In scope\n10: \n11: | Item | Detail |\n12: |------|--------|\n13: | **Module path** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` |\n14: | **Source reference** | `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` |\n15: | **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1` |\n16: | **Resource types** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` |\n17: | **Clientset** | `Interface` with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor; `Discovery()` and typed client accessors |\n18: | **Typed clients** | Full CRUD + Watch + Patch for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n19: | **Informers** | `SharedInformerFactory` with namespace-scoped informers |\n20: | **Listers** | `AgentRuntimeLister`, `CodeInterpreterLister` with namespace support |\n21: | **Fake clients** | Test doubles for all typed clients and clientset |\n22: | **Scheme registration** | `AddToScheme` for `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n23: | **Makefile targets** | `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh` using k8s.io/code-generator v0.34.1 |\n24: \n25: ### Out of scope\n26: \n27: - Custom resource definitions (CRDs) ŌĆö handled by separate AR\n28: - Controller implementation using the generated client\n29: - Client authentication / config handling beyond standard client-go patterns\n30: - Client-rate limiting or custom retry logic\n31: - Integration with Volcano scheduler\n32: - Versioned API (v1beta1 or other versions) ŌĆö v1alpha1 only for this AR\n33: \n34: ## Design\n35: \n36: ### File layout\n37: \n38: | Path | Role |\n39: |------|------|\n40: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n41: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n42: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n43: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n44: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n45: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n46: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n47: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n48: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n49: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n50: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n51: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n52: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n53: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n54: | `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n55: | `client-go/informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n56: | `client-go/informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n57: | `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n58: | `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n59: | `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n60: | `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n61: | `client-go/informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n62: | `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n63: | `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n64: | `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n65: \n66: ### Code generation\n67: \n68: **Command**: `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n69: \n70: ```bash\n71: #!/bin/bash\n72: # hack/update-codegen.sh\n73: \n74: set -e\n75: \n76: CODEGEN_VERSION=\"v0.34.1\"\n77: MODULE_PATH=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n78: SOURCE_DIR=\"/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go\"\n79: \n80: go install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/client-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n81: go install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/lister-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n82: go install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/informer-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n83: \n84: client-gen \\\n85:     --input-base=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\" \\\n86:     --input=\"runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n87:     --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset\" \\\n88:     --clientset-name=\"versioned\" \\\n89:     --with-watch=true \\\n90:     --apply-configuration-package=\"k8s.io/client-go/applyconfiguration\"\n91: \n92: lister-gen \\\n93:     --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n94:     --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\"\n95: \n96: informer-gen \\\n97:     --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n98:     --versioned-clientset-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset/versioned\" \\\n99:     --listers-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\" \\\n100:     --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/informers\"\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### Clientset interface\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type Interface interface {\n107:     Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n108:     RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n109: }\n110: \n111: type Clientset struct {\n112:     *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n113:     runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n114: }\n115: \n116: func NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)\n117: func NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)\n118: func NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset\n119: func New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset\n120: ```\n121: \n122: ### Typed client interfaces\n123: \n124: **AgentRuntimeInterface**:\n125: ```go\n126: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n127:     RESTClient() rest.Interface\n128:     Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n129:     Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n130:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n131:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n132:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n133:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n134:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n135:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n136:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n137:     AgentRuntimeExpansion\n138: }\n139: ```\n140: \n141: REST resource plural: `agentruntimes`\n142: \n143: **CodeInterpreterInterface**: Same method shape for `CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: `codeinterpreters`\n144: \n145: ### Informer factory\n146: \n147: ```go\n148: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n149:     Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n150:     Shutdown()\n151:     WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n152:     ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n153:     InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n154:     Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n155: }\n156: \n157: func NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)\n158: func NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration, options ...SharedInformerOption)\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### Lister interfaces\n162: \n163: ```go\n164: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n165:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n166:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n167:     AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n168: }\n169: \n170: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n171:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n172:     Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n173:     AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n174: }\n175: ```\n176: \n177: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`.\n178: \n179: ## Impact analysis\n180: \n181: ### Files created\n182: \n183: | File | Lines (est.) |\n184: |------|-------------|\n185: | `client-go/` directory | ~2500 lines (generated) |\n186: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | ~30 lines |\n187: | `Makefile` additions | ~10 lines |\n188: \n189: ### Files modified\n190: \n191: | File | Change |\n192: |------|--------|\n193: | `Makefile` | Add `gen-client` target |\n194: | `go.mod` (client-go) | Add client-go dependencies |\n195: \n196: ### Dependencies\n197: \n198: | Dependency | Usage |\n199: |------------|-------|\n200: | `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 | Code generation tools |\n201: | `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API definitions |\n202: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes type utilities |\n203: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Client generation base |\n204: | `k8s.io/utils` | Utility functions |\n205: \n206: ### Downstream consumers\n207: \n208: | Consumer | Dependency |\n209: |----------|-----------|\n210: | `cmd/router` | Imports `client-go` for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter management |\n211: | `test/e2e` | Uses fake clients for controller testing |\n212: | Future controllers | Use listers and informers for caching |\n213: \n214: ### Breaking change risk\n215: \n216: **Low**: This is a new module. Existing code may need to import and use the new client-go module, but no existing functionality is modified.\n217: \n218: ### Performance characteristics\n219: \n220: - **Generation time**: ~10-30 seconds for full client generation\n221: - **Client runtime**: Standard client-go performance (caching, watch, retry)\n222: - **Binary size**: Generated code adds ~500KB to client-go module\n223: - **Informer memory**: Depends on cluster size; uses standard Kubernetes informer caching\n224: \n225: ### Edge cases handled\n226: \n227: 1. **Watch support**: Enabled via `--with-watch=true` for real-time resource updates\n228: 2. **Fake clients**: Full test doubles for unit testing without cluster access\n229: 3. **Namespace-scoped operations**: Both namespaced and cluster-scoped listers provided\n230: 4. **Patch operations**: Support for strategic merge patch and JSON patch\n231: 5. **Expansion interfaces**: Empty expansion interfaces reserved for future custom methods\n232: \n233: ## Alternatives considered\n234: \n235: ### 1. Manual client implementation\n236: \n237: **Approach**: Write typed clients manually without code generation.\n238: \n239: **Rejected because**:\n240: - Violates Kubernetes ecosystem conventions; harder for others to maintain\n241: - Code generator ensures consistency with upstream client-go patterns\n242: - Manual maintenance burden for CRUD operations, especially with watch/patch\n243: - Missing automatic fake client generation requires manual test double maintenance\n244: \n245: ### 2. Use controller-runtime client\n246: \n247: **Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` instead of generating client-go.\n248: \n249: **Rejected because**:\n250: - Router component uses client-go patterns (based on Kubernetes sample controller)\n251: - Existing codebase already imports client-go; consistency within project\n252: - controller-runtime client is untyped (uses `Object` interface); typed clients provide better IDE support\n253: - Informers and listers not provided by controller-runtime by default\n254: \n255: ### 3. Generate only typed clients, skip informers/listers\n256: \n257: **Approach**: Client generation without informer and lister generation.\n258: \n259: **Rejected because**:\n260: - Informers provide significant performance benefits for repeated reads (caching)\n261: - Listers provide namespace-scoped caching with consistent indexers\n262: - Router's expected usage pattern involves watching resources and caching for lookups\n263: - Fake informers needed for controller unit tests\n264: \n265: ### 4. Use kubebuilder/operator-sdk\n266: \n267: **Approach**: Use kubebuilder to scaffold and generate clients.\n268: \n269: **Rejected because**:\n270: - AgentCube does not follow kubebuilder project layout\n271: - Would require significant restructuring of existing codebase\n272: - kubebuilder generates controllers + webhooks; only client needed here\n273: - Overhead of kubebuilder annotations for simple client generation\n274: \n275: ### 5. Skip fake clients\n276: \n277: **Approach**: Generate only real clients, no fake implementations.\n278: \n279: **Rejected because**:\n280: - Unit tests require fake clients to avoid cluster dependencies\n281: - Standard Kubernetes client-go package includes fake clients by convention\n282: - E2E and integration tests depend on fake clients for isolated testing\n283: - Minimal overhead: fake generation is automatic with main client generation\n\n(End of file - total 283 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-035 ŌĆö client-go ń▒╗Õ×ŗÕ«óµłĘń½»ńö¤µłÉ\n\n## Purpose\n\nGenerate Kubernetes client code (client-go) for AgentCube's API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, enabling in-cluster clients to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. This generated client follows the standard Kubernetes client-go patterns, providing typed clients, listers, informers, and fake clients for testing. The client library will be consumed by the Router component to manage agent runtimes and code interpreters programmatically.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` |\n| **Source reference** | `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1` |\n| **Resource types** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` |\n| **Clientset** | `Interface` with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor; `Discovery()` and typed client accessors |\n| **Typed clients** | Full CRUD + Watch + Patch for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n| **Informers** | `SharedInformerFactory` with namespace-scoped informers |\n| **Listers** | `AgentRuntimeLister`, `CodeInterpreterLister` with namespace support |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775884565258,"end":1775884565267}}}}
