{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775884569077,"sessionID":"ses_2850888eeffe6nUnso1RhMHTNb","part":{"id":"prt_d7af809f3001qI6JITpMCi1mJ4","messageID":"msg_d7af7fb4d0015b0z6d9fnUGhGj","sessionID":"ses_2850888eeffe6nUnso1RhMHTNb","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884638621,"sessionID":"ses_2850888eeffe6nUnso1RhMHTNb","part":{"id":"prt_d7af80f15001x201JLFI04cHTC","messageID":"msg_d7af7fb4d0015b0z6d9fnUGhGj","sessionID":"ses_2850888eeffe6nUnso1RhMHTNb","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_260a9646c46545d8847b4d80","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","newString":"# AR-041 ŌĆö E2E Integration Testing\n\n## Purpose\n\nEstablish an End-to-End (E2E) integration testing framework for the agentcube project to validate the complete lifecycle of `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources through the generated client-go library. This framework will ensure that the client implementation works correctly in real cluster scenarios, controllers behave as expected when handling resource operations, and the system provides reliable programmatic interfaces for external consumers.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `test/e2e` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Test framework** | Go `testing` package with custom helpers |\n| **Target resources** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n| **Test scenarios** | CRUD operations, status updates, watch events, informer synchronization |\n| **Test environment** | Kubernetes cluster (kind for local, configurable for CI) |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Performance benchmarking and load testing\n- Chaos testing and fault injection\n- Multi-cluster scenarios and federation\n- Upgrade and migration testing\n- Unit tests for individual controllers (handled separately)\n- Stress testing and concurrency testing\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated Kubernetes client (from AR-035) |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | REST client utilities |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Type utilities and metav1 |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` | Optional: for controller integration tests |\n| `k8s.io/klog` | Logging |\n\n## Design\n\n### Test directory structure\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ README.md                      # Test documentation\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Makefile                       # Test execution targets\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ go.mod                         # Module definition\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ go.sum\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ main_test.go                   # Test suite initialization\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ setup_test.go                  # Environment setup/teardown\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentruntime_test.go           # AgentRuntime E2E tests\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ codeinterpreter_test.go        # CodeInterpreter E2E tests\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ helpers/\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ client.go                  # Client initialization helpers\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ fixtures.go                # Test fixture generators\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cleanup.go                 # Resource cleanup utilities\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ wait.go                    # Wait utilities for async operations\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ scripts/\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ setup-kind.sh              # Kind cluster setup script\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ teardown-kind.sh           # Kind cluster teardown\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ run-e2e.sh                 # Test execution wrapper\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ config/\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ e2e-config.yaml            # Test configuration\n```\n\n### Test organization\n\n**Main test file (main_test.go)**:\n```go\nfunc TestMain(m *testing.M) {\n    // Parse flags\n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    // Setup test environment\n    cfg, err := config.GetConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get config: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Create client\n    clientset, err := versioned.NewForConfig(cfg)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create clientset: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Register cleanup\n    exitCode := m.Run()\n    \n    // Cleanup\n    os.Exit(exitCode)\n}\n```\n\n### Test patterns\n\n**CRUD test pattern**:\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    namespace := \"e2e-test-\" + uuid.New().String()\n    \n    // Create\n    ar := fixtures.NewAgentRuntime(namespace, \"test-runtime\")\n    created, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    require.NotNil(t, created)\n    \n    // Read\n    fetched, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, created.Name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, ar.Name, fetched.Name)\n    \n    // Update\n    fetched.Spec.Image = \"updated-image\"\n    updated, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update(ctx, fetched, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"updated-image\", updated.Spec.Image)\n    \n    // Delete\n    err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, created.Name, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n}\n```\n\n**Watch test pattern**:\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeWatch(t *testing.T) {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n    defer cancel()\n    \n    watchClient, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    defer watchClient.Stop()\n    \n    // Create resource\n    ar := fixtures.NewAgentRuntime(namespace, \"watch-test\")\n    _, err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Wait for event\n    select {\n    case event := <-watchClient.ResultChan():\n        assert.Equal(t, watch.Added, event.Type)\n        assert.Equal(t, ar.Name, event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime).Name)\n    case <-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n        t.Fatal(\"Timeout waiting for watch event\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Test fixtures\n\n```go\n// fixtures.go\npackage fixtures\n\nfunc NewAgentRuntime(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      name,\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            Image: \"agent-runtime:latest\",\n            Resources: corev1.ResourceRequirements{\n                Limits: corev1.ResourceList{\n                    corev1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"256Mi\"),\n                    corev1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"500m\"),\n                },\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n\nfunc NewCodeInterpreter(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      name,\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n            Image: \"code-interpreter:latest\",\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Test execution\n\n**Makefile targets**:\n```makefile\n.PHONY: e2e-test e2e-setup e2e-teardown\n\ne2e-test: ## Run E2E tests\n\tgo test -v ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n\ne2e-test-verbose: ## Run E2E tests with verbose output\n\tgo test -v -count=1 ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n\ne2e-setup: ## Setup E2E test environment\n\t./test/e2e/scripts/setup-kind.sh\n\ne2e-teardown: ## Teardown E2E test environment\n\t./test/e2e/scripts/teardown-kind.sh\n```\n\n### CI integration\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/e2e.yaml\nname: E2E Tests\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main]\n\njobs:\n  e2e:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - name: Setup kind\n        run: ./test/e2e/scripts/setup-kind.sh\n      - name: Run E2E tests\n        run: go test -v ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n      - name: Teardown kind\n        if: always()\n        run: ./test/e2e/scripts/teardown-kind.sh\n```\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `test/e2e/README.md` | Test documentation |\n| `test/e2e/Makefile` | Test execution targets |\n| `test/e2e/go.mod` | Module definition |\n| `test/e2e/main_test.go` | Test suite initialization |\n| `test/e2e/setup_test.go` | Environment setup |\n| `test/e2e/agentruntime_test.go` | AgentRuntime tests (~200 lines) |\n| `test/e2e/codeinterpreter_test.go` | CodeInterpreter tests (~200 lines) |\n| `test/e2e/helpers/*.go` | Test helpers (~150 lines) |\n| `test/e2e/scripts/*.sh` | Environment scripts (~100 lines) |\n\n**Estimated total**: ~800 lines\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `Makefile` | Add `e2e-test` target to root Makefile |\n| `.github/workflows/` | Add E2E test workflow |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| client-go | ^0.34.0 | Kubernetes client |\n| apimachinery | ^0.34.0 | Type utilities |\n| klog | ^2.0.0 | Logging |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| CI/CD pipelines | Uses E2E tests for regression detection |\n| Development workflow | Developers run tests before submitting PRs |\n| Release process | E2E tests must pass before release |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**Low**: This is a new test module. Existing functionality is not modified. Tests may need updates when API types change, but this is expected behavior.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **Test execution time**: ~5-15 minutes for full suite\n- **Parallelization**: Can be parallelized by namespace\n- **Resource usage**: Requires running Kubernetes cluster (kind uses ~2GB RAM)\n- **Cleanup**: Automatic cleanup after each test\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Test isolation**: Each test uses unique namespace to avoid conflicts\n2. **Cleanup on failure**: Deferred cleanup ensures resources are removed\n3. **Timeout handling**: Watch operations have explicit timeouts\n4. **Cluster availability**: Tests check cluster connectivity before running\n5. **Resource quota**: Tests respect namespace resource limits\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Use Ginkgo/Gomega BDD framework\n\n**Approach**: Use Ginkgo for BDD-style tests with Gomega matchers.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Adds additional dependency and learning curve for team\n- Standard Go testing is sufficient for this use case\n- Team familiarity with standard testing package\n- Less overhead for simple CRUD validation\n\n### 2. Use Kubernetes e2e framework\n\n**Approach**: Use `k8s.io/kubernetes/test/e2e` framework from Kubernetes core.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Heavyweight dependency (>100MB)\n- Steep learning curve and complex configuration\n- Overkill for simple resource CRUD testing\n- Requires full Kubernetes build infrastructure\n\n### 3. Use Operator SDK test framework\n\n**Approach**: Use `operator-sdk test` for testing.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Operator SDK assumes kubebuilder project layout\n- Adds unnecessary abstraction layer\n- May not integrate well with existing client-go only setup\n- Additional tooling requirements\n\n### 4. Use controller-runtime envtest\n\n**Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest` for API server-less testing.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- envtest is best for controller unit tests\n- E2E tests should test against real Kubernetes cluster\n- Want to validate actual API server interaction\n- Controller logic tested separately from E2E\n\n### 5. Skip E2E tests, rely only on unit tests\n\n**Approach**: Only use fake clients for testing without real cluster.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Fake clients don't catch real-world integration issues\n- Can't validate actual API server behavior\n- No validation of CRD schema and validation\n- Customer use cases require real cluster testing","oldString":"# AR-035 ŌĆö client-go ń▒╗Õ×ŗÕ«óµłĘń½»ńö¤µłÉ\n\n## Purpose\n\nGenerate Kubernetes client code (client-go) for AgentCube's API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, enabling in-cluster clients to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. This generated client follows the standard Kubernetes client-go patterns, providing typed clients, listers, informers, and fake clients for testing. The client library will be consumed by the Router component to manage agent runtimes and code interpreters programmatically.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` |\n| **Source reference** | `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1` |\n| **Resource types** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` |\n| **Clientset** | `Interface` with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor; `Discovery()` and typed client accessors |\n| **Typed clients** | Full CRUD + Watch + Patch for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n| **Informers** | `SharedInformerFactory` with namespace-scoped informers |\n| **Listers** | `AgentRuntimeLister`, `CodeInterpreterLister` with namespace support |\n| **Fake clients** | Test doubles for all typed clients and clientset |\n| **Scheme registration** | `AddToScheme` for `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n| **Makefile targets** | `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh` using k8s.io/code-generator v0.34.1 |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Custom resource definitions (CRDs) ŌĆö handled by separate AR\n- Controller implementation using the generated client\n- Client authentication / config handling beyond standard client-go patterns\n- Client-rate limiting or custom retry logic\n- Integration with Volcano scheduler\n- Versioned API (v1beta1 or other versions) ŌĆö v1alpha1 only for this AR\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n\n### Code generation\n\n**Command**: `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# hack/update-codegen.sh\n\nset -e\n\nCODEGEN_VERSION=\"v0.34.1\"\nMODULE_PATH=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\nSOURCE_DIR=\"/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go\"\n\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/client-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/lister-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/informer-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n\nclient-gen \\\n    --input-base=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\" \\\n    --input=\"runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset\" \\\n    --clientset-name=\"versioned\" \\\n    --with-watch=true \\\n    --apply-configuration-package=\"k8s.io/client-go/applyconfiguration\"\n\nlister-gen \\\n    --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\"\n\ninformer-gen \\\n    --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --versioned-clientset-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset/versioned\" \\\n    --listers-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/informers\"\n```\n\n### Clientset interface\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n    Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n    RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n\ntype Clientset struct {\n    *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n    runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n}\n\nfunc NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)\nfunc NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)\nfunc NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset\nfunc New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset\n```\n\n### Typed client interfaces\n\n**AgentRuntimeInterface**:\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    RESTClient() rest.Interface\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeExpansion\n}\n```\n\nREST resource plural: `agentruntimes`\n\n**CodeInterpreterInterface**: Same method shape for `CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: `codeinterpreters`\n\n### Informer factory\n\n```go\ntype SharedInformerFactory interface {\n    Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n    Shutdown()\n    WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n    ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n    InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n}\n\nfunc NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)\nfunc NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration, options ...SharedInformerOption)\n```\n\n### Lister interfaces\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n    AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n}\n```\n\nSame pattern for `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`.\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `client-go/` directory | ~2500 lines (generated) |\n| `hack/update-codegen.sh` | ~30 lines |\n| `Makefile` additions | ~10 lines |\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `Makefile` | Add `gen-client` target |\n| `go.mod` (client-go) | Add client-go dependencies |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 | Code generation tools |\n| `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API definitions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes type utilities |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Client generation base |\n| `k8s.io/utils` | Utility functions |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `cmd/router` | Imports `client-go` for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter management |\n| `test/e2e` | Uses fake clients for controller testing |\n| Future controllers | Use listers and informers for caching |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**Low**: This is a new module. Existing code may need to import and use the new client-go module, but no existing functionality is modified.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **Generation time**: ~10-30 seconds for full client generation\n- **Client runtime**: Standard client-go performance (caching, watch, retry)\n- **Binary size**: Generated code adds ~500KB to client-go module\n- **Informer memory**: Depends on cluster size; uses standard Kubernetes informer caching\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Watch support**: Enabled via `--with-watch=true` for real-time resource updates\n2. **Fake clients**: Full test doubles for unit testing without cluster access\n3. **Namespace-scoped operations**: Both namespaced and cluster-scoped listers provided\n4. **Patch operations**: Support for strategic merge patch and JSON patch\n5. **Expansion interfaces**: Empty expansion interfaces reserved for future custom methods\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Manual client implementation\n\n**Approach**: Write typed clients manually without code generation.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Violates Kubernetes ecosystem conventions; harder for others to maintain\n- Code generator ensures consistency with upstream client-go patterns\n- Manual maintenance burden for CRUD operations, especially with watch/patch\n- Missing automatic fake client generation requires manual test double maintenance\n\n### 2. Use controller-runtime client\n\n**Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` instead of generating client-go.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Router component uses client-go patterns (based on Kubernetes sample controller)\n- Existing codebase already imports client-go; consistency within project\n- controller-runtime client is untyped (uses `Object` interface); typed clients provide better IDE support\n- Informers and listers not provided by controller-runtime by default\n\n### 3. Generate only typed clients, skip informers/listers\n\n**Approach**: Client generation without informer and lister generation.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Informers provide significant performance benefits for repeated reads (caching)\n- Listers provide namespace-scoped caching with consistent indexers\n- Router's expected usage pattern involves watching resources and caching for lookups\n- Fake informers needed for controller unit tests\n\n### 4. Use kubebuilder/operator-sdk\n\n**Approach**: Use kubebuilder to scaffold and generate clients.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- AgentCube does not follow kubebuilder project layout\n- Would require significant restructuring of existing codebase\n- kubebuilder generates controllers + webhooks; only client needed here\n- Overhead of kubebuilder annotations for simple client generation\n\n### 5. Skip fake clients\n\n**Approach**: Generate only real clients, no fake implementations.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Unit tests require fake clients to avoid cluster dependencies\n- Standard Kubernetes client-go package includes fake clients by convention\n- E2E and integration tests depend on fake clients for isolated testing\n- Minimal overhead: fake generation is automatic with main client generation"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\n@@ -1,283 +1,342 @@\n-# AR-035 ŌĆö client-go ń▒╗Õ×ŗÕ«óµłĘń½»ńö¤µłÉ\n+# AR-041 ŌĆö E2E Integration Testing\n \n ## Purpose\n \n-Generate Kubernetes client code (client-go) for AgentCube's API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, enabling in-cluster clients to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. This generated client follows the standard Kubernetes client-go patterns, providing typed clients, listers, informers, and fake clients for testing. The client library will be consumed by the Router component to manage agent runtimes and code interpreters programmatically.\n+Establish an End-to-End (E2E) integration testing framework for the agentcube project to validate the complete lifecycle of `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources through the generated client-go library. This framework will ensure that the client implementation works correctly in real cluster scenarios, controllers behave as expected when handling resource operations, and the system provides reliable programmatic interfaces for external consumers.\n \n ## Scope\n \n ### In scope\n \n | Item | Detail |\n |------|--------|\n-| **Module path** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` |\n-| **Source reference** | `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` |\n-| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1` |\n-| **Resource types** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` |\n-| **Clientset** | `Interface` with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor; `Discovery()` and typed client accessors |\n-| **Typed clients** | Full CRUD + Watch + Patch for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n-| **Informers** | `SharedInformerFactory` with namespace-scoped informers |\n-| **Listers** | `AgentRuntimeLister`, `CodeInterpreterLister` with namespace support |\n-| **Fake clients** | Test doubles for all typed clients and clientset |\n-| **Scheme registration** | `AddToScheme` for `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n-| **Makefile targets** | `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh` using k8s.io/code-generator v0.34.1 |\n+| **Module path** | `test/e2e` |\n+| **Language** | Go |\n+| **Test framework** | Go `testing` package with custom helpers |\n+| **Target resources** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n+| **Test scenarios** | CRUD operations, status updates, watch events, informer synchronization |\n+| **Test environment** | Kubernetes cluster (kind for local, configurable for CI) |\n \n ### Out of scope\n \n-- Custom resource definitions (CRDs) ŌĆö handled by separate AR\n-- Controller implementation using the generated client\n-- Client authentication / config handling beyond standard client-go patterns\n-- Client-rate limiting or custom retry logic\n-- Integration with Volcano scheduler\n-- Versioned API (v1beta1 or other versions) ŌĆö v1alpha1 only for this AR\n+- Performance benchmarking and load testing\n+- Chaos testing and fault injection\n+- Multi-cluster scenarios and federation\n+- Upgrade and migration testing\n+- Unit tests for individual controllers (handled separately)\n+- Stress testing and concurrency testing\n \n-## Design\n+### Dependencies\n \n-### File layout\n+| Dependency | Usage |\n+|------------|-------|\n+| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated Kubernetes client (from AR-035) |\n+| `k8s.io/client-go` | REST client utilities |\n+| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Type utilities and metav1 |\n+| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` | Optional: for controller integration tests |\n+| `k8s.io/klog` | Logging |\n \n-| Path | Role |\n-|------|------|\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n-| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n-| `client-go/informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n-| `client-go/informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n-| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n-| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n-| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n-| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n-| `client-go/informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n-| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n-| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n-| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n+## Design\n \n-### Code generation\n+### Test directory structure\n \n-**Command**: `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n+```\n+test/e2e/\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ README.md                      # Test documentation\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Makefile                       # Test execution targets\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ go.mod                         # Module definition\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ go.sum\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ main_test.go                   # Test suite initialization\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ setup_test.go                  # Environment setup/teardown\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentruntime_test.go           # AgentRuntime E2E tests\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ codeinterpreter_test.go        # CodeInterpreter E2E tests\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ helpers/\n+Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ client.go                  # Client initialization helpers\n+Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ fixtures.go                # Test fixture generators\n+Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cleanup.go                 # Resource cleanup utilities\n+Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ wait.go                    # Wait utilities for async operations\n+Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ scripts/\n+Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ setup-kind.sh              # Kind cluster setup script\n+Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ teardown-kind.sh           # Kind cluster teardown\n+Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ run-e2e.sh                 # Test execution wrapper\n+ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ config/\n+    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ e2e-config.yaml            # Test configuration\n+```\n \n-```bash\n-#!/bin/bash\n-# hack/update-codegen.sh\n+### Test organization\n \n-set -e\n-\n-CODEGEN_VERSION=\"v0.34.1\"\n-MODULE_PATH=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n-SOURCE_DIR=\"/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go\"\n-\n-go install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/client-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n-go install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/lister-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n-go install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/informer-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n-\n-client-gen \\\n-    --input-base=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\" \\\n-    --input=\"runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n-    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset\" \\\n-    --clientset-name=\"versioned\" \\\n-    --with-watch=true \\\n-    --apply-configuration-package=\"k8s.io/client-go/applyconfiguration\"\n-\n-lister-gen \\\n-    --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n-    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\"\n-\n-informer-gen \\\n-    --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n-    --versioned-clientset-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset/versioned\" \\\n-    --listers-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\" \\\n-    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/informers\"\n+**Main test file (main_test.go)**:\n+```go\n+func TestMain(m *testing.M) {\n+    // Parse flags\n+    flag.Parse()\n+    \n+    // Setup test environment\n+    cfg, err := config.GetConfig()\n+    if err != nil {\n+        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get config: %v\", err)\n+    }\n+    \n+    // Create client\n+    clientset, err := versioned.NewForConfig(cfg)\n+    if err != nil {\n+        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create clientset: %v\", err)\n+    }\n+    \n+    // Register cleanup\n+    exitCode := m.Run()\n+    \n+    // Cleanup\n+    os.Exit(exitCode)\n+}\n ```\n \n-### Clientset interface\n+### Test patterns\n \n+**CRUD test pattern**:\n ```go\n-type Interface interface {\n-    Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n-    RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n+func TestAgentRuntimeLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n+    ctx := context.Background()\n+    namespace := \"e2e-test-\" + uuid.New().String()\n+    \n+    // Create\n+    ar := fixtures.NewAgentRuntime(namespace, \"test-runtime\")\n+    created, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n+    require.NoError(t, err)\n+    require.NotNil(t, created)\n+    \n+    // Read\n+    fetched, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, created.Name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n+    require.NoError(t, err)\n+    assert.Equal(t, ar.Name, fetched.Name)\n+    \n+    // Update\n+    fetched.Spec.Image = \"updated-image\"\n+    updated, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update(ctx, fetched, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n+    require.NoError(t, err)\n+    assert.Equal(t, \"updated-image\", updated.Spec.Image)\n+    \n+    // Delete\n+    err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, created.Name, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n+    require.NoError(t, err)\n }\n+```\n \n-type Clientset struct {\n-    *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n-    runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n+**Watch test pattern**:\n+```go\n+func TestAgentRuntimeWatch(t *testing.T) {\n+    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n+    defer cancel()\n+    \n+    watchClient, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n+    require.NoError(t, err)\n+    defer watchClient.Stop()\n+    \n+    // Create resource\n+    ar := fixtures.NewAgentRuntime(namespace, \"watch-test\")\n+    _, err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n+    require.NoError(t, err)\n+    \n+    // Wait for event\n+    select {\n+    case event := <-watchClient.ResultChan():\n+        assert.Equal(t, watch.Added, event.Type)\n+        assert.Equal(t, ar.Name, event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime).Name)\n+    case <-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n+        t.Fatal(\"Timeout waiting for watch event\")\n+    }\n }\n-\n-func NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)\n-func NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)\n-func NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset\n-func New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset\n ```\n \n-### Typed client interfaces\n+### Test fixtures\n \n-**AgentRuntimeInterface**:\n ```go\n-type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n-    RESTClient() rest.Interface\n-    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n-    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n-    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n-    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n-    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n-    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n-    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n-    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n-    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n-    AgentRuntimeExpansion\n+// fixtures.go\n+package fixtures\n+\n+func NewAgentRuntime(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n+    return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n+        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n+            Name:      name,\n+            Namespace: namespace,\n+        },\n+        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n+            Image: \"agent-runtime:latest\",\n+            Resources: corev1.ResourceRequirements{\n+                Limits: corev1.ResourceList{\n+                    corev1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"256Mi\"),\n+                    corev1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"500m\"),\n+                },\n+            },\n+        },\n+    }\n }\n+\n+func NewCodeInterpreter(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter {\n+    return &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n+        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n+            Name:      name,\n+            Namespace: namespace,\n+        },\n+        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n+            Image: \"code-interpreter:latest\",\n+        },\n+    }\n+}\n ```\n \n-REST resource plural: `agentruntimes`\n+### Test execution\n \n-**CodeInterpreterInterface**: Same method shape for `CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: `codeinterpreters`\n+**Makefile targets**:\n+```makefile\n+.PHONY: e2e-test e2e-setup e2e-teardown\n \n-### Informer factory\n+e2e-test: ## Run E2E tests\n+\tgo test -v ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n \n-```go\n-type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n-    Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n-    Shutdown()\n-    WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n-    ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n-    InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n-    Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n-}\n+e2e-test-verbose: ## Run E2E tests with verbose output\n+\tgo test -v -count=1 ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n \n-func NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)\n-func NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration, options ...SharedInformerOption)\n+e2e-setup: ## Setup E2E test environment\n+\t./test/e2e/scripts/setup-kind.sh\n+\n+e2e-teardown: ## Teardown E2E test environment\n+\t./test/e2e/scripts/teardown-kind.sh\n ```\n \n-### Lister interfaces\n+### CI integration\n \n-```go\n-type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n-    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n-    AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n-    AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n-}\n+```yaml\n+# .github/workflows/e2e.yaml\n+name: E2E Tests\n+on:\n+  push:\n+    branches: [main]\n+  pull_request:\n+    branches: [main]\n \n-type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n-    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n-    Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n-    AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n-}\n+jobs:\n+  e2e:\n+    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n+    steps:\n+      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n+      - name: Setup kind\n+        run: ./test/e2e/scripts/setup-kind.sh\n+      - name: Run E2E tests\n+        run: go test -v ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n+      - name: Teardown kind\n+        if: always()\n+        run: ./test/e2e/scripts/teardown-kind.sh\n ```\n \n-Same pattern for `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`.\n-\n ## Impact analysis\n \n ### Files created\n \n-| File | Lines (est.) |\n+| File | Description |\n |------|-------------|\n-| `client-go/` directory | ~2500 lines (generated) |\n-| `hack/update-codegen.sh` | ~30 lines |\n-| `Makefile` additions | ~10 lines |\n+| `test/e2e/README.md` | Test documentation |\n+| `test/e2e/Makefile` | Test execution targets |\n+| `test/e2e/go.mod` | Module definition |\n+| `test/e2e/main_test.go` | Test suite initialization |\n+| `test/e2e/setup_test.go` | Environment setup |\n+| `test/e2e/agentruntime_test.go` | AgentRuntime tests (~200 lines) |\n+| `test/e2e/codeinterpreter_test.go` | CodeInterpreter tests (~200 lines) |\n+| `test/e2e/helpers/*.go` | Test helpers (~150 lines) |\n+| `test/e2e/scripts/*.sh` | Environment scripts (~100 lines) |\n \n+**Estimated total**: ~800 lines\n+\n ### Files modified\n \n | File | Change |\n |------|--------|\n-| `Makefile` | Add `gen-client` target |\n-| `go.mod` (client-go) | Add client-go dependencies |\n+| `Makefile` | Add `e2e-test` target to root Makefile |\n+| `.github/workflows/` | Add E2E test workflow |\n \n ### Dependencies\n \n-| Dependency | Usage |\n-|------------|-------|\n-| `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 | Code generation tools |\n-| `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API definitions |\n-| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes type utilities |\n-| `k8s.io/client-go` | Client generation base |\n-| `k8s.io/utils` | Utility functions |\n+| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n+|------------|---------|---------|\n+| client-go | ^0.34.0 | Kubernetes client |\n+| apimachinery | ^0.34.0 | Type utilities |\n+| klog | ^2.0.0 | Logging |\n \n ### Downstream consumers\n \n | Consumer | Dependency |\n |----------|-----------|\n-| `cmd/router` | Imports `client-go` for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter management |\n-| `test/e2e` | Uses fake clients for controller testing |\n-| Future controllers | Use listers and informers for caching |\n+| CI/CD pipelines | Uses E2E tests for regression detection |\n+| Development workflow | Developers run tests before submitting PRs |\n+| Release process | E2E tests must pass before release |\n \n ### Breaking change risk\n \n-**Low**: This is a new module. Existing code may need to import and use the new client-go module, but no existing functionality is modified.\n+**Low**: This is a new test module. Existing functionality is not modified. Tests may need updates when API types change, but this is expected behavior.\n \n ### Performance characteristics\n \n-- **Generation time**: ~10-30 seconds for full client generation\n-- **Client runtime**: Standard client-go performance (caching, watch, retry)\n-- **Binary size**: Generated code adds ~500KB to client-go module\n-- **Informer memory**: Depends on cluster size; uses standard Kubernetes informer caching\n+- **Test execution time**: ~5-15 minutes for full suite\n+- **Parallelization**: Can be parallelized by namespace\n+- **Resource usage**: Requires running Kubernetes cluster (kind uses ~2GB RAM)\n+- **Cleanup**: Automatic cleanup after each test\n \n ### Edge cases handled\n \n-1. **Watch support**: Enabled via `--with-watch=true` for real-time resource updates\n-2. **Fake clients**: Full test doubles for unit testing without cluster access\n-3. **Namespace-scoped operations**: Both namespaced and cluster-scoped listers provided\n-4. **Patch operations**: Support for strategic merge patch and JSON patch\n-5. **Expansion interfaces**: Empty expansion interfaces reserved for future custom methods\n+1. **Test isolation**: Each test uses unique namespace to avoid conflicts\n+2. **Cleanup on failure**: Deferred cleanup ensures resources are removed\n+3. **Timeout handling**: Watch operations have explicit timeouts\n+4. **Cluster availability**: Tests check cluster connectivity before running\n+5. **Resource quota**: Tests respect namespace resource limits\n \n ## Alternatives considered\n \n-### 1. Manual client implementation\n+### 1. Use Ginkgo/Gomega BDD framework\n \n-**Approach**: Write typed clients manually without code generation.\n+**Approach**: Use Ginkgo for BDD-style tests with Gomega matchers.\n \n **Rejected because**:\n-- Violates Kubernetes ecosystem conventions; harder for others to maintain\n-- Code generator ensures consistency with upstream client-go patterns\n-- Manual maintenance burden for CRUD operations, especially with watch/patch\n-- Missing automatic fake client generation requires manual test double maintenance\n+- Adds additional dependency and learning curve for team\n+- Standard Go testing is sufficient for this use case\n+- Team familiarity with standard testing package\n+- Less overhead for simple CRUD validation\n \n-### 2. Use controller-runtime client\n+### 2. Use Kubernetes e2e framework\n \n-**Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` instead of generating client-go.\n+**Approach**: Use `k8s.io/kubernetes/test/e2e` framework from Kubernetes core.\n \n **Rejected because**:\n-- Router component uses client-go patterns (based on Kubernetes sample controller)\n-- Existing codebase already imports client-go; consistency within project\n-- controller-runtime client is untyped (uses `Object` interface); typed clients provide better IDE support\n-- Informers and listers not provided by controller-runtime by default\n+- Heavyweight dependency (>100MB)\n+- Steep learning curve and complex configuration\n+- Overkill for simple resource CRUD testing\n+- Requires full Kubernetes build infrastructure\n \n-### 3. Generate only typed clients, skip informers/listers\n+### 3. Use Operator SDK test framework\n \n-**Approach**: Client generation without informer and lister generation.\n+**Approach**: Use `operator-sdk test` for testing.\n \n **Rejected because**:\n-- Informers provide significant performance benefits for repeated reads (caching)\n-- Listers provide namespace-scoped caching with consistent indexers\n-- Router's expected usage pattern involves watching resources and caching for lookups\n-- Fake informers needed for controller unit tests\n+- Operator SDK assumes kubebuilder project layout\n+- Adds unnecessary abstraction layer\n+- May not integrate well with existing client-go only setup\n+- Additional tooling requirements\n \n-### 4. Use kubebuilder/operator-sdk\n+### 4. Use controller-runtime envtest\n \n-**Approach**: Use kubebuilder to scaffold and generate clients.\n+**Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest` for API server-less testing.\n \n **Rejected because**:\n-- AgentCube does not follow kubebuilder project layout\n-- Would require significant restructuring of existing codebase\n-- kubebuilder generates controllers + webhooks; only client needed here\n-- Overhead of kubebuilder annotations for simple client generation\n+- envtest is best for controller unit tests\n+- E2E tests should test against real Kubernetes cluster\n+- Want to validate actual API server interaction\n+- Controller logic tested separately from E2E\n \n-### 5. Skip fake clients\n+### 5. Skip E2E tests, rely only on unit tests\n \n-**Approach**: Generate only real clients, no fake implementations.\n+**Approach**: Only use fake clients for testing without real cluster.\n \n **Rejected because**:\n-- Unit tests require fake clients to avoid cluster dependencies\n-- Standard Kubernetes client-go package includes fake clients by convention\n-- E2E and integration tests depend on fake clients for isolated testing\n-- Minimal overhead: fake generation is automatic with main client generation\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+- Fake clients don't catch real-world integration issues\n+- Can't validate actual API server behavior\n+- No validation of CRD schema and validation\n+- Customer use cases require real cluster testing\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","before":"# AR-035 ŌĆö client-go ń▒╗Õ×ŗÕ«óµłĘń½»ńö¤µłÉ\n\n## Purpose\n\nGenerate Kubernetes client code (client-go) for AgentCube's API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, enabling in-cluster clients to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. This generated client follows the standard Kubernetes client-go patterns, providing typed clients, listers, informers, and fake clients for testing. The client library will be consumed by the Router component to manage agent runtimes and code interpreters programmatically.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` |\n| **Source reference** | `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1` |\n| **Resource types** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` |\n| **Clientset** | `Interface` with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor; `Discovery()` and typed client accessors |\n| **Typed clients** | Full CRUD + Watch + Patch for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\n| **Informers** | `SharedInformerFactory` with namespace-scoped informers |\n| **Listers** | `AgentRuntimeLister`, `CodeInterpreterLister` with namespace support |\n| **Fake clients** | Test doubles for all typed clients and clientset |\n| **Scheme registration** | `AddToScheme` for `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n| **Makefile targets** | `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh` using k8s.io/code-generator v0.34.1 |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Custom resource definitions (CRDs) ŌĆö handled by separate AR\n- Controller implementation using the generated client\n- Client authentication / config handling beyond standard client-go patterns\n- Client-rate limiting or custom retry logic\n- Integration with Volcano scheduler\n- Versioned API (v1beta1 or other versions) ŌĆö v1alpha1 only for this AR\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n| `client-go/informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n| `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n\n### Code generation\n\n**Command**: `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# hack/update-codegen.sh\n\nset -e\n\nCODEGEN_VERSION=\"v0.34.1\"\nMODULE_PATH=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\nSOURCE_DIR=\"/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go\"\n\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/client-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/lister-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\ngo install k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/informer-gen@${CODEGEN_VERSION}\n\nclient-gen \\\n    --input-base=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\" \\\n    --input=\"runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset\" \\\n    --clientset-name=\"versioned\" \\\n    --with-watch=true \\\n    --apply-configuration-package=\"k8s.io/client-go/applyconfiguration\"\n\nlister-gen \\\n    --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\"\n\ninformer-gen \\\n    --input-dirs=\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" \\\n    --versioned-clientset-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/clientset/versioned\" \\\n    --listers-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/listers\" \\\n    --output-package=\"${MODULE_PATH}/informers\"\n```\n\n### Clientset interface\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n    Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n    RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n\ntype Clientset struct {\n    *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n    runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n}\n\nfunc NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)\nfunc NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)\nfunc NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset\nfunc New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset\n```\n\n### Typed client interfaces\n\n**AgentRuntimeInterface**:\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    RESTClient() rest.Interface\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeExpansion\n}\n```\n\nREST resource plural: `agentruntimes`\n\n**CodeInterpreterInterface**: Same method shape for `CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: `codeinterpreters`\n\n### Informer factory\n\n```go\ntype SharedInformerFactory interface {\n    Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n    Shutdown()\n    WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n    ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n    InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n}\n\nfunc NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)\nfunc NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration, options ...SharedInformerOption)\n```\n\n### Lister interfaces\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n    AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n}\n```\n\nSame pattern for `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister`.\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `client-go/` directory | ~2500 lines (generated) |\n| `hack/update-codegen.sh` | ~30 lines |\n| `Makefile` additions | ~10 lines |\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `Makefile` | Add `gen-client` target |\n| `go.mod` (client-go) | Add client-go dependencies |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 | Code generation tools |\n| `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API definitions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes type utilities |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Client generation base |\n| `k8s.io/utils` | Utility functions |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `cmd/router` | Imports `client-go` for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter management |\n| `test/e2e` | Uses fake clients for controller testing |\n| Future controllers | Use listers and informers for caching |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**Low**: This is a new module. Existing code may need to import and use the new client-go module, but no existing functionality is modified.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **Generation time**: ~10-30 seconds for full client generation\n- **Client runtime**: Standard client-go performance (caching, watch, retry)\n- **Binary size**: Generated code adds ~500KB to client-go module\n- **Informer memory**: Depends on cluster size; uses standard Kubernetes informer caching\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Watch support**: Enabled via `--with-watch=true` for real-time resource updates\n2. **Fake clients**: Full test doubles for unit testing without cluster access\n3. **Namespace-scoped operations**: Both namespaced and cluster-scoped listers provided\n4. **Patch operations**: Support for strategic merge patch and JSON patch\n5. **Expansion interfaces**: Empty expansion interfaces reserved for future custom methods\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Manual client implementation\n\n**Approach**: Write typed clients manually without code generation.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Violates Kubernetes ecosystem conventions; harder for others to maintain\n- Code generator ensures consistency with upstream client-go patterns\n- Manual maintenance burden for CRUD operations, especially with watch/patch\n- Missing automatic fake client generation requires manual test double maintenance\n\n### 2. Use controller-runtime client\n\n**Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` instead of generating client-go.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Router component uses client-go patterns (based on Kubernetes sample controller)\n- Existing codebase already imports client-go; consistency within project\n- controller-runtime client is untyped (uses `Object` interface); typed clients provide better IDE support\n- Informers and listers not provided by controller-runtime by default\n\n### 3. Generate only typed clients, skip informers/listers\n\n**Approach**: Client generation without informer and lister generation.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Informers provide significant performance benefits for repeated reads (caching)\n- Listers provide namespace-scoped caching with consistent indexers\n- Router's expected usage pattern involves watching resources and caching for lookups\n- Fake informers needed for controller unit tests\n\n### 4. Use kubebuilder/operator-sdk\n\n**Approach**: Use kubebuilder to scaffold and generate clients.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- AgentCube does not follow kubebuilder project layout\n- Would require significant restructuring of existing codebase\n- kubebuilder generates controllers + webhooks; only client needed here\n- Overhead of kubebuilder annotations for simple client generation\n\n### 5. Skip fake clients\n\n**Approach**: Generate only real clients, no fake implementations.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Unit tests require fake clients to avoid cluster dependencies\n- Standard Kubernetes client-go package includes fake clients by convention\n- E2E and integration tests depend on fake clients for isolated testing\n- Minimal overhead: fake generation is automatic with main client generation","after":"# AR-041 ŌĆö E2E Integration Testing\n\n## Purpose\n\nEstablish an End-to-End (E2E) integration testing framework for the agentcube project to validate the complete lifecycle of `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources through the generated client-go library. This framework will ensure that the client implementation works correctly in real cluster scenarios, controllers behave as expected when handling resource operations, and the system provides reliable programmatic interfaces for external consumers.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `test/e2e` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Test framework** | Go `testing` package with custom helpers |\n| **Target resources** | `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter` (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1) |\n| **Test scenarios** | CRUD operations, status updates, watch events, informer synchronization |\n| **Test environment** | Kubernetes cluster (kind for local, configurable for CI) |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Performance benchmarking and load testing\n- Chaos testing and fault injection\n- Multi-cluster scenarios and federation\n- Upgrade and migration testing\n- Unit tests for individual controllers (handled separately)\n- Stress testing and concurrency testing\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated Kubernetes client (from AR-035) |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | REST client utilities |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Type utilities and metav1 |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client` | Optional: for controller integration tests |\n| `k8s.io/klog` | Logging |\n\n## Design\n\n### Test directory structure\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ README.md                      # Test documentation\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ Makefile                       # Test execution targets\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ go.mod                         # Module definition\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ go.sum\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ main_test.go                   # Test suite initialization\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ setup_test.go                  # Environment setup/teardown\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentruntime_test.go           # AgentRuntime E2E tests\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ codeinterpreter_test.go        # CodeInterpreter E2E tests\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ helpers/\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ client.go                  # Client initialization helpers\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ fixtures.go                # Test fixture generators\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cleanup.go                 # Resource cleanup utilities\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ wait.go                    # Wait utilities for async operations\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ scripts/\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ setup-kind.sh              # Kind cluster setup script\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ teardown-kind.sh           # Kind cluster teardown\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ run-e2e.sh                 # Test execution wrapper\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ config/\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ e2e-config.yaml            # Test configuration\n```\n\n### Test organization\n\n**Main test file (main_test.go)**:\n```go\nfunc TestMain(m *testing.M) {\n    // Parse flags\n    flag.Parse()\n    \n    // Setup test environment\n    cfg, err := config.GetConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get config: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Create client\n    clientset, err := versioned.NewForConfig(cfg)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create clientset: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Register cleanup\n    exitCode := m.Run()\n    \n    // Cleanup\n    os.Exit(exitCode)\n}\n```\n\n### Test patterns\n\n**CRUD test pattern**:\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    namespace := \"e2e-test-\" + uuid.New().String()\n    \n    // Create\n    ar := fixtures.NewAgentRuntime(namespace, \"test-runtime\")\n    created, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    require.NotNil(t, created)\n    \n    // Read\n    fetched, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, created.Name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, ar.Name, fetched.Name)\n    \n    // Update\n    fetched.Spec.Image = \"updated-image\"\n    updated, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update(ctx, fetched, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"updated-image\", updated.Spec.Image)\n    \n    // Delete\n    err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, created.Name, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n}\n```\n\n**Watch test pattern**:\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeWatch(t *testing.T) {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n    defer cancel()\n    \n    watchClient, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    defer watchClient.Stop()\n    \n    // Create resource\n    ar := fixtures.NewAgentRuntime(namespace, \"watch-test\")\n    _, err = clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Wait for event\n    select {\n    case event := <-watchClient.ResultChan():\n        assert.Equal(t, watch.Added, event.Type)\n        assert.Equal(t, ar.Name, event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime).Name)\n    case <-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n        t.Fatal(\"Timeout waiting for watch event\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Test fixtures\n\n```go\n// fixtures.go\npackage fixtures\n\nfunc NewAgentRuntime(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      name,\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            Image: \"agent-runtime:latest\",\n            Resources: corev1.ResourceRequirements{\n                Limits: corev1.ResourceList{\n                    corev1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"256Mi\"),\n                    corev1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"500m\"),\n                },\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n\nfunc NewCodeInterpreter(namespace, name string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      name,\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n            Image: \"code-interpreter:latest\",\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Test execution\n\n**Makefile targets**:\n```makefile\n.PHONY: e2e-test e2e-setup e2e-teardown\n\ne2e-test: ## Run E2E tests\n\tgo test -v ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n\ne2e-test-verbose: ## Run E2E tests with verbose output\n\tgo test -v -count=1 ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n\ne2e-setup: ## Setup E2E test environment\n\t./test/e2e/scripts/setup-kind.sh\n\ne2e-teardown: ## Teardown E2E test environment\n\t./test/e2e/scripts/teardown-kind.sh\n```\n\n### CI integration\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/e2e.yaml\nname: E2E Tests\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main]\n\njobs:\n  e2e:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - name: Setup kind\n        run: ./test/e2e/scripts/setup-kind.sh\n      - name: Run E2E tests\n        run: go test -v ./test/e2e/... -timeout=30m\n      - name: Teardown kind\n        if: always()\n        run: ./test/e2e/scripts/teardown-kind.sh\n```\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `test/e2e/README.md` | Test documentation |\n| `test/e2e/Makefile` | Test execution targets |\n| `test/e2e/go.mod` | Module definition |\n| `test/e2e/main_test.go` | Test suite initialization |\n| `test/e2e/setup_test.go` | Environment setup |\n| `test/e2e/agentruntime_test.go` | AgentRuntime tests (~200 lines) |\n| `test/e2e/codeinterpreter_test.go` | CodeInterpreter tests (~200 lines) |\n| `test/e2e/helpers/*.go` | Test helpers (~150 lines) |\n| `test/e2e/scripts/*.sh` | Environment scripts (~100 lines) |\n\n**Estimated total**: ~800 lines\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `Makefile` | Add `e2e-test` target to root Makefile |\n| `.github/workflows/` | Add E2E test workflow |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| client-go | ^0.34.0 | Kubernetes client |\n| apimachinery | ^0.34.0 | Type utilities |\n| klog | ^2.0.0 | Logging |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| CI/CD pipelines | Uses E2E tests for regression detection |\n| Development workflow | Developers run tests before submitting PRs |\n| Release process | E2E tests must pass before release |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**Low**: This is a new test module. Existing functionality is not modified. Tests may need updates when API types change, but this is expected behavior.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **Test execution time**: ~5-15 minutes for full suite\n- **Parallelization**: Can be parallelized by namespace\n- **Resource usage**: Requires running Kubernetes cluster (kind uses ~2GB RAM)\n- **Cleanup**: Automatic cleanup after each test\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Test isolation**: Each test uses unique namespace to avoid conflicts\n2. **Cleanup on failure**: Deferred cleanup ensures resources are removed\n3. **Timeout handling**: Watch operations have explicit timeouts\n4. **Cluster availability**: Tests check cluster connectivity before running\n5. **Resource quota**: Tests respect namespace resource limits\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Use Ginkgo/Gomega BDD framework\n\n**Approach**: Use Ginkgo for BDD-style tests with Gomega matchers.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Adds additional dependency and learning curve for team\n- Standard Go testing is sufficient for this use case\n- Team familiarity with standard testing package\n- Less overhead for simple CRUD validation\n\n### 2. Use Kubernetes e2e framework\n\n**Approach**: Use `k8s.io/kubernetes/test/e2e` framework from Kubernetes core.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Heavyweight dependency (>100MB)\n- Steep learning curve and complex configuration\n- Overkill for simple resource CRUD testing\n- Requires full Kubernetes build infrastructure\n\n### 3. Use Operator SDK test framework\n\n**Approach**: Use `operator-sdk test` for testing.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Operator SDK assumes kubebuilder project layout\n- Adds unnecessary abstraction layer\n- May not integrate well with existing client-go only setup\n- Additional tooling requirements\n\n### 4. Use controller-runtime envtest\n\n**Approach**: Use `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest` for API server-less testing.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- envtest is best for controller unit tests\n- E2E tests should test against real Kubernetes cluster\n- Want to validate actual API server interaction\n- Controller logic tested separately from E2E\n\n### 5. Skip E2E tests, rely only on unit tests\n\n**Approach**: Only use fake clients for testing without real cluster.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Fake clients don't catch real-world integration issues\n- Can't validate actual API server behavior\n- No validation of CRD schema and validation\n- Customer use cases require real cluster testing","additions":249,"deletions":190},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775884638495,"end":1775884638616}}}}
